A connected component means:A group where every node can reach every other node.
1 --- 2

3 --- 4
Here:
1 and 2 connected
3 and 4 connected

If I start DFS from one node, it visits the ENTIRE connected group.
So:
first DFS = first component
second DFS = second component

CODE-
for(int i=0;i<V;i++) //traverse the graph 
{
    if(!vis[i]) //new component found 
    {
        count++; //count the component 

        dfs(i); //apply the recursive function, vist all the graph 
    }
}
